Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech at the Harry S. Truman Building in Washington, D.C., honoring the friendship and importance of the relationship between India and the United States. She highlighted the impact of Indian Americans in various fields, including politics, business, and entertainment. Harris shared personal anecdotes about her visits to India and the influence of her grandfather on her interest in public service. She also praised India's global impact in areas such as healthcare, technology, and space exploration. Prime Minister Modi responded by expressing his gratitude for the warm welcome and emphasized the need for deeper cooperation between India and the United States. He highlighted the strong people-to-people ties between the two countries and commended Harris and Secretary Blinken for their contributions to the strategic partnership. Modi emphasized the progress made in various areas of cooperation and expressed optimism about the future of the India-U.S. relationship.